### Simple Loan API - Sample Requests
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or copy as curl commands

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Submit Valid Application
POST {{baseUrl}}/applications
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "income": 50000,
  "amount": 15000
}

### Submit Low Income Application (should be rejected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/applications
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "income": 25000,
  "amount": 10000
}

### Submit Application with High Amount
POST {{baseUrl}}/applications
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Rich",
  "lastName": "Person",
  "email": "rich@example.com",
  "income": 28000,
  "amount": 45000
}

### Submit Invalid Application
POST {{baseUrl}}/applications
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Bad",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "income": -5000,
  "amount": 0
}

### Boundary Test - Exact Min Income ($30k)
POST {{baseUrl}}/applications
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Boundary",
  "lastName": "Test",
  "email": "boundary@example.com",
  "income": 30000,
  "amount": 5000
}

### Get All Applications
GET {{baseUrl}}/applications

### Get Specific Application (use ID from POST response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/applications/APP-001

### Get Non-existent Application
GET {{baseUrl}}/applications/APP-999

### Update Application Status
PUT {{baseUrl}}/applications/APP-001/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "funded"
}

### Invalid Status Update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/applications/APP-001/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "invalid-status"
}